WEBVTT

00:03.274 --> 00:05.136
YEAH, WE FOUND HIM IN TOWN,
NO I.D.,

00:05.136 --> 00:06.477
ON SOME KIND OF RANT --

00:06.477 --> 00:09.180
SAYS THE C.I.A.
SENT ASSASSINS TO KILL HIM.

00:09.180 --> 00:12.043
PARANOID DELUSIONS,
HALLUCINATIONS -- THANKS.

00:12.043 --> 00:13.144
ANOTHER FRIDAY NIGHT,
HUH?

00:13.144 --> 00:15.346
HEY, BUDDY.
WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

00:15.346 --> 00:16.687
OH,
I CAN'T TELL YOU THAT.

00:16.687 --> 00:17.788
IT'S TOO DANGEROUS --
FOR YOU, FOR ME,

00:17.788 --> 00:19.220
FOR EVERYONE
IN THIS BUILDING.

00:19.220 --> 00:20.721
IF YOU WANT TO
CALL ME SOMETHING,

00:20.721 --> 00:21.752
CALL ME "DAN."

00:21.752 --> 00:23.754
OKAY, DAN.

00:23.754 --> 00:26.297
YOU, UH --
YOU WANT A STICK OF GUM?

00:26.297 --> 00:27.528
ALWAYS CALMS MY NERVES.

00:27.528 --> 00:29.430
AND ROTS YOUR TEETH.
NO.

00:29.430 --> 00:30.601
[ CHUCKLES ]

00:30.601 --> 00:32.403
WELCOME TO
JERSEYVILLE PSYCHIATRIC.

00:32.403 --> 00:35.636
WE'RE GONNA TAKE YOU
TO YOUR ROOM NOW, OKAY?

00:48.619 --> 00:53.084
LIFE CAN BE AWFULLY GRIM...

00:53.084 --> 00:56.127
DEATH, TAXES...

00:56.127 --> 00:57.628
THE CUBS OUT OF CONTENTION
BY AUGUST.

00:57.628 --> 00:58.729
[ LAUGHTER ]

00:58.729 --> 01:00.791
IT'S ALL SO INEVITABLE...

01:00.791 --> 01:02.793
UNLESS WE HAVE HOPE.

01:02.793 --> 01:07.798
THEN, THE BRAIN CAN ENVISION
WHAT'S POSSIBLE.

01:07.798 --> 01:11.142
HUMANITY...
MIND-BLOWING SEX...

01:11.142 --> 01:12.673
THE WORLD SERIES AT WRIGLEY --

01:12.673 --> 01:14.675
NOW I'M PUSHING IT.

01:14.675 --> 01:17.208
[ LAUGHTER ]
MAYBE THAT'S PUSHING IT.

01:17.208 --> 01:19.550
BUT HOPE ABOUNDS
IN THE WORLD OF NEUROTHERAPY,

01:19.550 --> 01:21.712
THANKS TO EMBRYONIC CELLS
IN THE BRAIN KNOWN --

01:21.712 --> 01:24.815
KNOWN AS NEUROBLASTS.

01:26.487 --> 01:28.659
THESE TINY MIRACLES FORM

01:28.659 --> 01:31.192
IN THE SUBVENTRICULAR ZONE
AFTER A STROKE,

01:31.192 --> 01:33.464
THEN ZIP OVER
TO THE DAMAGED TISSUE

01:33.464 --> 01:34.865
AND MAKE REPAIRS.

01:34.865 --> 01:36.197
AMAZING.

01:36.197 --> 01:40.601
THE BRAIN
HAS ITS OWN PIT CREW.

01:40.601 --> 01:44.205
NOW, NEUROBLAST RESEARCH
IS STILL IN ITS INFANCY.

01:44.205 --> 01:46.237
BUT THIS WEEKEND, MR. LEWICKI
WILL GETTING TOGETHER

01:46.237 --> 01:48.839
WITH SOME OF HIS FELLOW
GRAD STUDENTS IN ANN ARBOR

01:48.839 --> 01:50.711
TO DISCUSS THE POSSIBILITY.

01:50.711 --> 01:52.283
THINK ABOUT IT --

01:52.283 --> 01:55.146
SOMEDAY, INSTEAD OF MANAGING
BRAIN DEGENERATION

01:55.146 --> 01:56.487
WITH MEDICATION,

01:56.487 --> 02:01.822
WE MAY BE ABLE TO HELP THE BRAIN
HEAL ITSELF.

02:01.822 --> 02:03.394
A LECTURE ON OPTIMISM --

02:03.394 --> 02:05.726
GOD, THAT MAKES ME WANT TO
GO BACK TO COLLEGE.

02:05.726 --> 02:08.329
ENDLESS NIGHTS
IN THE DORM,

02:08.329 --> 02:10.331
GORGING OURSELVES
ON HOAGIES,

02:10.331 --> 02:11.532
SO STONED
THAT WE COULD HARDLY --

02:11.532 --> 02:12.763
RUBEN, I'M SURE
YOU DIDN'T COME HERE

02:12.763 --> 02:15.236
TO RELIVE
YOUR WASTED YOUTH.

02:15.236 --> 02:16.567
YOU'RE RIGHT.
I-I NEED YOUR HELP.

02:16.567 --> 02:19.370
THIS IS MY CLIENT,
ERICA BEECHER.

02:19.370 --> 02:22.413
SHE'S A PATIENT AT JERSEYVILLE
PSYCHIATRIC HOSPITAL.

02:22.413 --> 02:26.677
SHE ALLEGEDLY STABBED A NURSE
TO DEATH WITH A LETTER OPENER.

02:26.677 --> 02:28.219
JERSEYVILLE'S A HELLHOLE.

02:28.219 --> 02:29.880
STATE SHUT IT DOWN TWICE
WHEN I WAS IN COLLEGE --

02:29.880 --> 02:32.253
UNSANITARY CONDITIONS,
PATIENT ABUSE.

02:32.253 --> 02:33.484
WAS THAT HER MOTIVE?

02:33.484 --> 02:34.855
I HAVE NO IDEA.
SHE WON'T TALK TO ME.

02:34.855 --> 02:37.228
SHE WON'T LET ME SEE
HER PSYCH RECORDS.
WHY?

02:37.228 --> 02:38.629
SHE'S MENTALLY ILL?

02:38.629 --> 02:40.791
I'LL PROBABLY
PLEAD HER GUILTY

02:40.791 --> 02:42.663
IN EXCHANGE
FOR PSYCHIATRIC CARE,

02:42.663 --> 02:46.337
BUT I CAN'T GO TO THE JUDGE
WITHOUT AN EXPERT DIAGNOSIS.

02:46.337 --> 02:47.568
WELL, I'LL ASSESS HER,
BUT IF SHE HASN'T TALKED TO YOU,

02:47.568 --> 02:49.270
HOW DO YOU KNOW
SHE'S EVEN GUILTY,

02:49.270 --> 02:51.772
OR THAT SHE'S SERIOUSLY
MENTALLY ILL, FOR THAT MATTER?

02:51.772 --> 02:53.774
THEY FOUND HER WITH
THE NURSE'S BLOOD ON HER HANDS.

02:53.774 --> 02:57.478
OH, AND I THINK THIS ANSWERS
YOUR SECOND QUESTION.

03:01.712 --> 03:04.785
SHE SWALLOWED
THE MURDER WEAPON.

03:04.785 --> 03:07.488
I WANT YOU CLOSING OUT
THE REGISTER.

03:07.488 --> 03:08.819
PETE CAN HANDLE
ALL THE SIDE WORK,

03:08.819 --> 03:09.920
EXCEPT THE GARNISH.

03:09.920 --> 03:11.792
THE KID HAS NO ATTENTION
TO DETAIL.

03:11.792 --> 03:13.664
WE'LL BE FINE.
HEY, DID YOU PACK A SWIMSUIT?

03:13.664 --> 03:14.665
AUNT SHEILA'S GOT A POOL.

03:14.665 --> 03:16.367
I'M NOT GOING SWIMMING.

03:16.367 --> 03:17.528
WHY NOT?

03:17.528 --> 03:19.230
BECAUSE SHE EXPECTS YOU
TO KEEP VIGIL

03:19.230 --> 03:20.731
BY HER BEDSIDE
ALL WEEKEND?

03:20.731 --> 03:23.434
DAD, SHE'S GOT A BROKEN HIP.
SHE'S NOT DYING.

03:23.434 --> 03:24.775
BESIDES, YOU'RE
GOING TO SUNNY PHOENIX.

03:24.775 --> 03:26.307
YOU SHOULD PACK
A SWIMSUIT.

03:26.307 --> 03:27.808
YOUR OPINION IS NOTED.

03:27.808 --> 03:29.510
NOW, TAKE ME THROUGH IT.

03:29.510 --> 03:30.841
ARE YOU QUIZZING ME?

03:30.841 --> 03:32.743
HOW MANY SUMMERS
DID I WORK HERE?

03:32.743 --> 03:34.815
THAT WAS YEARS AGO,
KIDDO.

03:34.815 --> 03:37.518
OKAY -- PRINT OUT THE TAPE,
CHECK THE SALES,

03:37.518 --> 03:39.850
COUNT THE CASH,
ADD UP THE CREDIT-CARD RECEIPTS,

03:39.850 --> 03:41.952
CHECK THE TOTAL
AGAINST THE PRINTOUT.

03:41.952 --> 03:43.954
PUT THE TAPE RECEIPTS AND CASH
INTO THE SAFE.

03:43.954 --> 03:45.696
COMBINATION'S
STILL MY BIRTHDAY?

03:45.696 --> 03:47.358
[ CHUCKLES ]

03:47.358 --> 03:49.700
THE ANSWER IS TO YOUR QUESTION
IS FIVE SUMMERS --

03:49.700 --> 03:51.502
BEST TIME OF MY LIFE.

03:51.502 --> 03:55.005
DO YOU, UH,
REMEMBER ME, ERICA?

03:55.005 --> 03:56.737
I'M RUBEN BAUER,
YOUR LAWYER,

03:56.737 --> 03:59.009
AND I'VE BROUGHT MY FRIEND
DR. PIERCE TO TALK TO YOU.

03:59.009 --> 04:00.741
IT'S -- IT'S DANIEL.

04:00.741 --> 04:03.374
HOW'S YOUR THROAT? DOES IT
STILL HURT AFTER THE SURGERY?

04:03.374 --> 04:05.576
YOU GET USED TO IT.

04:05.576 --> 04:08.649
YOU'VE SWALLOWED
SHARP OBJECTS BEFORE.

04:08.649 --> 04:11.522
PENS AND PENCILS
ARE MY BREAD AND BUTTER.

04:11.522 --> 04:13.384
I'VE SWALLOWED NAILS, TOO...

04:14.425 --> 04:16.457
...SOME FORKS.

04:16.457 --> 04:18.629
DO YOU KNOW
WHY YOU DO IT?

04:18.629 --> 04:21.792
THE THOUGHT COMES INTO MY HEAD,
AND IT WON'T LEAVE ME ALONE.

04:23.434 --> 04:25.736
ONCE, I RIPPED THE ANTENNA
OFF A CAR AND SWALLOWED THAT.

04:25.736 --> 04:29.300
IT'S LIKE I DON'T
HAVE A CHOICE.

04:31.472 --> 04:33.344
I'VE BEEN WHERE YOU ARE.

04:33.344 --> 04:36.947
IT'S HARD TO KNOW
WHO TO TRUST.

04:36.947 --> 04:38.979
WE ARE ON YOUR SIDE.
WE WANT TO GET YOU OUT OF HERE.

04:38.979 --> 04:40.411
BUT YOU NEED TO TELL US

04:40.411 --> 04:42.282
WHAT HAPPENED
WITH THE LETTER OPENER.

04:45.416 --> 04:47.918
I STOLE IT.

04:47.918 --> 04:50.461
BUT I DIDN'T
KILL NURSE LAURIE.

04:50.461 --> 04:52.062
I SWEAR.

04:52.062 --> 04:54.925
I WAS DOING THERAPY
IN DR. POOLE'S OFFICE.

04:54.925 --> 04:58.469
HE SAID
I WAS MAKING PROGRESS.

04:58.469 --> 05:03.474
AND THEN I NOTICED
THE LETTER OPENER ON HIS DESK.

05:03.474 --> 05:07.738
AND I COULDN'T
STOP THINKING ABOUT IT.

05:07.738 --> 05:09.910
THEN,
NURSE LAURIE SHOWED UP.

05:09.910 --> 05:12.683
SHE SAID
THERE WAS A PROBLEM.

05:14.515 --> 05:16.016
AND WHEN THEY STEPPED OUT,
I JUST LIFTED IT.

05:19.490 --> 05:21.492
I DON'T KNOW IF NURSE LAURIE
SAW ME TAKE IT,

05:21.492 --> 05:23.654
BUT SHE MUST HAVE SEEN ME
HIDE IT UNDER MY MATTRESS,

05:23.654 --> 05:27.898
BECAUSE SHE CAME TO MY BEDROOM
THAT NIGHT, TOOK IT AWAY.

05:27.898 --> 05:30.461
BUT YOU MUST HAVE GOTTEN
THE LETTER OPENER BACK.

05:30.461 --> 05:32.032
I COULDN'T GET TO SLEEP.

05:32.032 --> 05:33.904
I KEPT THINKING HOW DISAPPOINTED
DR. POOLE WAS GONNA BE

05:33.904 --> 05:35.606
ONCE SHE TOLD HIM
WHAT I DID.

05:35.606 --> 05:38.469
I JUST WANTED TO ASK HER IF
I COULD BE THE ONE TO EXPLAIN.

05:41.111 --> 05:43.113
AND THEN I FOUND HER.

05:43.113 --> 05:46.447
SHE WAS LAYING IN A...

05:46.447 --> 05:50.120
PUDDLE OF BLOOD.

05:50.120 --> 05:53.984
THE LETTER OPENER WAS
STICKING OUT OF HER CHEST.

05:56.757 --> 05:58.459
I SHOULD HAVE RUN
FOR HELP,

05:58.459 --> 06:00.461
BUT THE THOUGHT
WAS IN MY HEAD,

06:00.461 --> 06:01.832
AND I COULDN'T ESCAPE IT.

06:01.832 --> 06:03.734
WHAT WAS THAT THOUGHT,
EXACTLY?

06:03.734 --> 06:06.066
IF I DIDN'T SWALLOW
THAT LETTER OPENER,

06:06.066 --> 06:07.668
I WAS GOING TO DIE.

06:16.106 --> 06:18.649
ERICA, YOU SAID
THAT NURSE LAURIE

06:18.649 --> 06:21.452
HAD A PROBLEM WITH DR. POOLE
EARLIER IN THE MORNING.

06:21.452 --> 06:22.653
DO YOU REMEMBER
WHAT IT WAS?

06:22.653 --> 06:24.515
NO -- I MEAN,
THEY WERE ARGUING, BUT --

06:24.515 --> 06:26.617
DID IT SOUND PERSONAL,
OR --

06:26.617 --> 06:28.659
DANIEL, COULD I HAVE
A WORD WITH YOU?

06:29.920 --> 06:32.623
I'M NOT THE F.B.I.,
DANIEL.

06:32.623 --> 06:35.626
I NEED YOU TO MAKE A DIAGNOSIS,
NOT TO PLAY DETECTIVE.

06:35.626 --> 06:38.128
WELL, HER DIAGNOSIS
SUGGESTS SHE'S INNOCENT.

06:38.128 --> 06:39.700
SHE SWALLOWED
THE LETTER OPENER

06:39.700 --> 06:41.832
BECAUSE SHE HAS
AN EXTREME CASE OF O.C.D.

06:41.832 --> 06:44.675
WHAT, LIKE SOMEONE WHO WASHES
HER HANDS OVER AND OVER?

06:44.675 --> 06:46.537
YES, EXCEPT ERICA
SWALLOWS SHARP OBJECTS.

06:46.537 --> 06:47.908
IT'S A COMPULSION.

06:47.908 --> 06:49.610
SHE DIDN'T DO IT AS PART
OF SOME CONSCIOUS PLAN

06:49.610 --> 06:50.781
TO COVER UP A MURDER.

06:50.781 --> 06:51.812
THE CHARGES ARE BOGUS.

06:51.812 --> 06:53.484
LOOK, FOR ALL YOU KNOW,

06:53.484 --> 06:55.415
ERICA GOT MAD WHEN THE NURSE
TOOK THE LETTER OPENER AWAY,

06:55.415 --> 06:56.847
AND SHE STABBED HER.

06:56.847 --> 06:59.820
THEN HER O.C.D. KICKED IN,
AND SHE SWALLOWED THE THING.

06:59.820 --> 07:02.192
I DON'T -- I DON'T THINK
THAT'S WHAT HAPPENED.

07:02.192 --> 07:03.894
YEAH, BUT ANY
SEMI-COMPETENT A.D.A.

07:03.894 --> 07:05.756
CAN CONVINCE A JURY
THAT IT DID.

07:05.756 --> 07:07.498
LOOK, I CAN'T RISK IT.

07:07.498 --> 07:10.501
IF WE LOSE AT TRIAL,
THEN ERICA HAS NO CHANCE

07:10.501 --> 07:11.662
OF GETTING THE CARE
THAT SHE NEEDS.

07:11.662 --> 07:12.903
BUT IF WE PLEAD GUILTY --

07:12.903 --> 07:14.064
THEN SHE SPENDS
THE REST OF HER LIFE

07:14.064 --> 07:15.606
IN A PSYCHIATRIC HOSPITAL

07:15.606 --> 07:17.538
WHEN IT'S POSSIBLE
SHE COULD BE CURED.

07:17.538 --> 07:20.511
CURED?
DANIEL, BE REALISTIC.

07:20.511 --> 07:22.843
THERE'S A PROCEDURE
AT CHICAGO GENERAL
CALLED GAMMA KNIFE.

07:22.843 --> 07:24.444
IT'S CONTROVERSIAL,

07:24.444 --> 07:26.116
BUT IT CAN AMELIORATE
THE EFFECTS OF O.C.D.

07:26.116 --> 07:27.548
IF WE CAN CLEAR HER
OF THIS MURDER,

07:27.548 --> 07:29.620
ERICA HAS A SHOT
AT A NORMAL LIFE.

07:29.620 --> 07:31.121
WE'D NEED
REASONABLE DOUBT --

07:31.121 --> 07:33.984
SOME ALTERNATIVE THEORY
OF THE CRIME.

07:33.984 --> 07:36.126
SO, LET'S START
INVESTIGATING.
HOW?

07:36.126 --> 07:38.659
NO PSYCH HOSPITAL
WITH A MURDER ON THEIR HANDS

07:38.659 --> 07:40.661
IS GONNA OPEN THEIR DOORS
TO A DEFENSE ATTORNEY.

07:40.661 --> 07:41.832
THEY'LL OPEN THEIR DOORS
TO THE F.B.I.

07:41.832 --> 07:43.634
I'LL CALL KATE RIGHT NOW.

07:43.634 --> 07:45.966
LOOK. [ SCOFFS ]
I KNOW SHE'S YOUR FRIEND.

07:45.966 --> 07:47.838
BUT THE F.B.I. WORKS
WITH PROSECUTORS,

07:47.838 --> 07:50.140
NOT DEFENSE ATTORNEYS.

07:50.140 --> 07:51.872
WE NEED
A DIFFERENT WAY IN.

07:55.145 --> 07:56.677
LOOK,
MY POINT TO HER IS,

07:56.677 --> 07:58.549
IF I CAN WATCH
HER HOME-MAKEOVER SHOWS...

07:58.549 --> 08:00.050
[ CHUCKLES ]
...SHE CAN
WEAR THE OCCASIONAL,

08:00.050 --> 08:03.213
YOU KNOW, SLUTTY OUTFIT
TO WATCH ME PLAY SOFTBALL.

08:03.213 --> 08:06.486
LOOK, NOTHING OBSCENE --
HELP ME! PLEASE! PLEASE!

08:06.486 --> 08:08.959
PLEASE, YOU HAVE TO HELP ME.
TH-THEY'RE TRYING TO KILL ME.

08:08.959 --> 08:11.221
ALL RIGHT, TAKE IT EASY.
WHO'S TRYING TO KILL YOU?

08:11.221 --> 08:14.064
THE C.I.A. THEY HAD --
THEY'VE HAD ASSASSINS
TRACKING ME FOR WEEKS.

08:14.064 --> 08:15.766
I JUST LOST TWO OF THEM
OUTSIDE OF TOWN.

08:15.766 --> 08:17.698
BUT IT'S ONLY -- IT'S ONLY
A MATTER OF TIME. OH, GOD.

08:17.698 --> 08:18.969
OKAY, JUST CALM DOWN.

08:18.969 --> 08:20.831
WE'RE GONNA TAKE YOU
SOMEPLACE SAFE.

08:20.831 --> 08:23.634
OKAY. THANK YOU.
THANK YOU.

08:36.817 --> 08:39.189
KATE!

08:39.189 --> 08:40.951
HEY!

08:40.951 --> 08:42.192
WHAT,
ARE YOU MOONLIGHTING?

08:42.192 --> 08:43.193
YEAH,
JUST FOR THE WEEKEND,

08:43.193 --> 08:44.555
BUT YOU DON'T
HAVE TO HIDE.

08:44.555 --> 08:45.826
MY DAD'S OUT OF TOWN.

08:45.826 --> 08:47.798
HE STILL WANT TO BREAK
MY FACE?

08:47.798 --> 08:49.600
OH, YEAH. COCKTAIL?

08:49.600 --> 08:50.831
PITCHER OF BLUE MOON.

08:50.831 --> 08:53.203
YOU GOT IT.

08:53.203 --> 08:56.206
BABYSITTING A COUPLE
OF BIGWIGS FROM D.C. --

08:56.206 --> 08:58.569
THEY LOVE THIS PLACE.

08:58.569 --> 08:59.910
HEY.

08:59.910 --> 09:01.241
SPEAKING OF INFIDELITY,

09:01.241 --> 09:04.575
I RAN INTO RUBEN BAUER
AT THE COURTHOUSE.

09:04.575 --> 09:06.216
AND THAT WAS ACTUALLY
YOUR SEGUE?

09:06.216 --> 09:08.619
HE TOLD ME HE'S GOT PIERCE
ON ONE OF HIS CASES.

09:09.549 --> 09:11.852
DOESN'T DANIEL KNOW BETTER THAN
TO WORK FOR A DEFENSE ATTORNEY?

09:11.852 --> 09:13.183
DANIEL CAN DO
WHATEVER HE WANTS.

09:13.183 --> 09:14.685
STOP TRYING
TO MAKE TROUBLE.

09:14.685 --> 09:16.556
OH, COME ON.
BAUER'S THE ENEMY.

09:16.556 --> 09:17.988
THAT'S GOT TO BOTHER YOU
A LITTLE.

09:17.988 --> 09:19.189
I DON'T KNOW.

09:19.189 --> 09:21.732
IF MY HUSBAND SLEPT
WITH MY BEST FRIEND,

09:21.732 --> 09:23.734
THAT MIGHT BOTHER ME,
BUT OTHERWISE,

09:23.734 --> 09:26.096
I TRY NOT TO SWEAT
THE SMALL STUFF.

09:31.742 --> 09:33.604
Natalie: I DON'T LIKE
THIS PLAN, DANIEL.

09:33.604 --> 09:36.176
DO YOU REMEMBER DAVID ROSENHAN
FROM THE 1970s?

09:36.176 --> 09:38.048
THE PSYCHOLOGIST
WHO CHECKED HIMSELF

09:38.048 --> 09:39.249
INTO A MENTAL INSTITUTION,

09:39.249 --> 09:40.911
PRETENDING TO BE
A SCHIZOPHRENIC.

09:40.911 --> 09:42.613
AND THEN HE GOT STUCK
FOR TWO MONTHS

09:42.613 --> 09:44.955
BECAUSE THEY DIDN'T BELIEVE
HE WAS FAKING IT.

09:44.955 --> 09:46.586
THAT'S NOT GONNA HAPPEN.

09:46.586 --> 09:48.258
RUBEN'S SPRINGING ME ON MONDAY.
YOU KNOW, IT'S JUST --

09:48.258 --> 09:50.661
IT'S A WEEKEND
WE'RE TALKING ABOUT HERE.

09:50.661 --> 09:52.122
PLEASE, TRY TO RELAX.

09:52.122 --> 09:53.824
IT'S NICER THAN YOU EXPECTED,
ISN'T IT?

09:53.824 --> 09:54.895
THEY MUST HAVE RENOVATED.

09:54.895 --> 09:55.966
IT'S STILL JERSEYVILLE.

09:55.966 --> 09:57.668
AND YOU'RE IN A LOCKED WARD

09:57.668 --> 09:59.099
WITH A KILLER
THAT YOU CAN'T IDENTIFY.

09:59.099 --> 10:01.331
AND ON TOP OF THAT,
YOU'VE DISRUPTED YOUR ROUTINE.

10:01.331 --> 10:03.003
I'M TRYING TO HELP ERICA.

10:03.003 --> 10:04.334
[ GROANS ]

10:04.334 --> 10:06.637
I'M -- HOW ABOUT
A LITTLE LESS HAND-WRINGING

10:06.637 --> 10:08.078
AND A LITTLE MORE HELPING ME
FIGURE OUT WHO KILLED THE NURSE?
[ DOOR OPENS ]

10:14.614 --> 10:18.018
GOOD MORNING, DAN.
THIS IS LEX.

10:18.018 --> 10:19.619
YOU'RE AT JERSEYVILLE
PSYCHIATRIC HOSPITAL.

10:19.619 --> 10:22.252
DO YOU REMEMBER
HOW YOU GOT HERE?

10:22.252 --> 10:23.954
THE POLICE.

10:23.954 --> 10:25.295
THAT'S RIGHT.

10:25.295 --> 10:27.397
YOU WERE A LITTLE CONFUSED
LAST NIGHT.

10:27.397 --> 10:29.700
LAST NIGHT
WAS A BAD NIGHT.

10:29.700 --> 10:31.361
WOULD YOU LIKE
TO GIVE US YOUR FULL NAME,

10:31.361 --> 10:33.633
OR SOMEONE YOU'D LIKE US
TO CONTACT FOR YOU?

10:33.633 --> 10:35.966
NOPE. NOPE.
NO, TOO DANGEROUS.

10:35.966 --> 10:38.138
I SEE. OKAY.

10:38.138 --> 10:40.771
HAVE YOU BEEN HEARING
ANY VOICES

10:40.771 --> 10:42.642
OR SEEN ANYTHING UNUSUAL
THIS MORNING?

10:42.642 --> 10:44.675
HE'S UNUSUAL.
OH.

10:44.675 --> 10:47.017
LEX IS
ONE OF OUR NURSES.

10:47.017 --> 10:48.879
HE'S GONNA GIVE YOU
YOUR MEDICATION,

10:48.879 --> 10:51.752
THEN TAKE YOU
TO GROUP THERAPY.

11:04.434 --> 11:06.136
YOU'RE PRETTY CALM, LEX.

11:06.136 --> 11:08.668
EVER SERVED AS AN OPERATIVE
IN A HOSTILE TERRITORY?

11:08.668 --> 11:12.202
NO. I'M JUST CALM.

11:12.202 --> 11:15.205
EVEN THOUGH ONE OF YOUR OWN WAS
MURDERED HERE THREE WEEKS AGO?

11:15.205 --> 11:17.207
WHO TOLD YOU THAT?
OH, COME ON.

11:17.207 --> 11:18.909
WE BOTH KNOW THAT'S
ABOVE YOUR CLEARANCE.

11:18.909 --> 11:21.381
Poole: NO. NO.
NOT TOMORROW -- TODAY.

11:21.381 --> 11:23.113
GET YOUR CHARTS
UP TO DATE.

11:24.184 --> 11:25.756
THE INVESTIGATOR'S
COMING AT 10:00.

11:25.756 --> 11:26.987
[ BEEP ]
GO.

11:26.987 --> 11:29.990
THAT'S DR. POOLE.

11:29.990 --> 11:34.324
YOU STAY ON HIS GOOD SIDE,
YOU'LL BE ALL RIGHT.

11:34.324 --> 11:37.027
Poole: WE HAVEN'T HEARD
FROM YOU ALL SESSION, DAN.

11:37.027 --> 11:39.029
TELL US
WHAT BRINGS YOU HERE.

11:39.029 --> 11:40.971
THAT'S --
THAT'S CLASSIFIED.

11:40.971 --> 11:43.974
LIAR.
ZOEY,
IT'S DAN'S FIRST DAY.

11:43.974 --> 11:46.006
MAYBE HE DOESN'T
FEEL SAFE YET.

11:46.006 --> 11:47.237
OR HE'S JUST LYING.

11:47.237 --> 11:48.839
[ MURMURING ]

11:48.839 --> 11:50.710
YOU THINK YOU'RE BETTER
THAN EVERYBODY ELSE?

11:50.710 --> 11:52.712
[ Viennese accent ]
THIS IS NOT HELPFUL.

11:52.712 --> 11:55.786
THERAPY WAS MEANT
FOR AN INDIVIDUAL,
NOT FOR THE GROUP.

11:55.786 --> 11:57.948
WHO ARE YOU SUPPOSED TO BE,
SIGMUND FREUD?

11:57.948 --> 12:00.420
NO, JUST ONE OF THE NUTJOBS,
CALLING YOU ON YOUR BULLSHIT.

12:00.420 --> 12:03.794
SO, NOW ONE MEMBER DECIDES
TO UNDERMINE THE LEADERSHIP,

12:03.794 --> 12:05.125
AND SO EVERYTHING
TURNS TO CHAOS.

12:05.125 --> 12:06.997
MM.

12:06.997 --> 12:10.130
LOOK AT THE TIME, DANIEL.
SHOULDN'T YOU BE GOING?

12:12.402 --> 12:15.405
UH, THE TRUTH IS,
I -- [ CLEARS THROAT ]

12:15.405 --> 12:17.367
I DON'T FEEL SAFE.

12:17.367 --> 12:19.139
GOOD, DAN.
TALK ABOUT THAT.

12:19.139 --> 12:20.510
I-I KNOW
THERE WAS A NURSE

12:20.510 --> 12:21.942
MURDERED IN THIS HOSPITAL
A FEW WEEKS AGO,

12:21.942 --> 12:23.213
A-AND THE KILLER'S
STILL AT LARGE.

12:23.213 --> 12:25.275
NOT YOUR AVERAGE ROOKIE,
EH, DR. POOLE?

12:25.275 --> 12:27.277
OKAY, VIRGIL.

12:27.277 --> 12:29.279
DAN, I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'VE HEARD

12:29.279 --> 12:32.182
OR WHO YOU'VE HEARD IT FROM,
BUT NOBODY IS AT LARGE.

12:32.182 --> 12:34.754
YOU ACTUALLY THINK ERICA
KILLED NURSE LAURIE?

12:34.754 --> 12:36.256
ZOEY --
SHE'S NOT
THAT KIND OF PERSON.

12:36.256 --> 12:38.458
SHE'S MY FRIEND.

12:38.458 --> 12:41.361
LET'S TALK ABOUT
YOUR TENDENCIES, DR. POOLE.

12:41.361 --> 12:42.833
ZOEY, THAT'S ENOUGH.

12:42.833 --> 12:44.334
YOU'RE A FASCIST.
KEEP TALKING, DANIEL.

12:44.334 --> 12:46.036
I THINK WE ARE CLOSE
TO A BREAKTHROUGH HERE.

12:46.036 --> 12:47.537
UH, I-I-I-I --

12:47.537 --> 12:50.500
I THINK THE REAL KILLER
I-I-IS IN THIS HOSPITAL.

12:50.500 --> 12:52.202
[ MURMURING ]

12:52.202 --> 12:53.904
MAYBE EVEN IN THIS ROOM.

12:56.907 --> 12:58.508
MAYBE IT WAS YOU,
DR. POOLE!

12:58.508 --> 13:00.150
[ LAUGHING ]

13:00.981 --> 13:04.815
ANTHONY.
ANTHONY! ANTHONY! SIT DOWN!

13:04.815 --> 13:07.117
[ SCREAMS ]

13:09.890 --> 13:13.063
HELP! HELP! THE PATIENTS
ARE ATTACKING DR. POOLE!

13:14.965 --> 13:19.129
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

13:20.400 --> 13:22.272
[ BEEP ]

13:22.272 --> 13:24.804
[ BUZZER ]

13:26.806 --> 13:28.478
HI.

13:28.478 --> 13:30.841
DR. POOLE'S HUNG UP IN GROUP
THERAPY, BUT HE -- HE KNEW

13:30.841 --> 13:32.843
HE WAS MEETING WITH YOU AT
10:00, SO HE SENT ME TO COVER.

13:32.843 --> 13:35.986
I'M -- I'M DR. LEWICKI.
KEVIN REYNOLDS, STATE BOARD.

13:35.986 --> 13:37.317
I JUST JOINED THE STAFF
A COUPLE WEEKS AGO,

13:37.317 --> 13:39.319
BUT DR. POOLE
NEVER MENTIONED

13:39.319 --> 13:41.321
AN INVESTIGATION
DURING THE INTERVIEW.

13:41.321 --> 13:43.493
THERE'S NOTHING TO WORRY ABOUT,
IS THERE?

13:43.493 --> 13:46.026
I CAN'T TALK ABOUT MY FINDINGS
BEFORE I GIVE THEM TO THE BOARD.

13:46.026 --> 13:47.357
THAT WOULD BE --
NO, NO, OF COURSE NOT.

13:47.357 --> 13:48.959
I JUST...
[ CHUCKLES ]

13:48.959 --> 13:51.101
MY WIFE FELL IN LOVE WITH
A HOUSE OVER THE WEEKEND.

13:51.101 --> 13:53.263
AND BEFORE
WE MAKE AN OFFER,

13:53.263 --> 13:54.604
I KIND OF NEED TO KNOW --
YOU UNDERSTAND.

13:54.604 --> 13:56.206
THERE YOU ARE.

13:56.206 --> 13:58.909
JENNA, TAKE MR. REYNOLDS
TO THE CONFERENCE ROOM.

13:58.909 --> 14:00.911
I NEED TO BORROW THE GOOD DOCTOR
FOR A FEW MINUTES,

14:00.911 --> 14:03.073
THEN I'LL CATCH UP.

14:03.073 --> 14:05.245
WE NEED TO TALK, DAN.

14:05.245 --> 14:08.278
[ BEEP ]
OR WOULD YOU PREFER
I CALL YOU DR. PIERCE?

14:18.188 --> 14:21.531
I RECOGNIZED YOU
RIGHT AWAY.

14:23.964 --> 14:27.137
I ALSO KNOW THE REAL REASON
YOU WON'T TELL ANYONE YOUR NAME.

14:29.269 --> 14:31.972
YOU'VE HAD A BRILLIANT CAREER
DESPITE YOUR MENTAL ILLNESS,

14:31.972 --> 14:33.303
BUT NOW YOU'VE RELAPSED,

14:33.303 --> 14:34.644
AND YOU'RE WORRIED
ABOUT YOUR REPUTATION

14:34.644 --> 14:36.346
IF PEOPLE FIND OUT
THAT YOU'RE HERE.

14:36.346 --> 14:38.348
I'M WORRIED ABOUT MY LIFE

14:38.348 --> 14:40.650
IF THE C.I.A.
FINDS OUT I'M HERE.

14:40.650 --> 14:42.352
THAT'S
A PARANOID FANTASY.

14:42.352 --> 14:45.215
YOUR MIND IS DISSOCIATING
FROM WHO YOU REALLY ARE

14:45.215 --> 14:48.418
AND WHAT THE REAL PRESSURES
ARE THAT YOU FACE.

14:48.418 --> 14:50.420
I'M SURE IT'S OVERWHELMING,
DR. PIERCE,

14:50.420 --> 14:52.592
BUT I CAN'T TREAT YOU
DIFFERENTLY FROM EVERYONE ELSE.

14:52.592 --> 14:56.066
IF YOU BREAK THE RULES,
THERE WILL BE CONSEQUENCES.

14:56.066 --> 14:58.228
I WAS ASSURED THAT
THIS FACILITY WAS SECURE,

14:58.228 --> 15:00.570
AND THEN THIS -- THIS
MEDICAL BOARD INVESTIGATOR

15:00.570 --> 15:02.432
WALTZES IN LIKE HE'S SHOPPING
FOR GROCERIES?

15:02.432 --> 15:04.374
HAS THE GUY
EVEN BEEN VETTED?

15:04.374 --> 15:06.536
DANIEL, I ASKED
THE INVESTIGATOR TO COME.

15:06.536 --> 15:08.338
WHY THE HELL
WOULD YOU DO THAT?

15:08.338 --> 15:11.041
THIS HOSPITAL
STILL LIVES IN THE SHADOW

15:11.041 --> 15:13.043
OF ITS REPUTATION
FROM 30 YEARS AGO.

15:13.043 --> 15:14.584
I'M SURE YOU KNOW
THE HISTORY.

15:14.584 --> 15:16.286
I BELIEVE IT AFFECTS
THE AMOUNT OF FUNDING

15:16.286 --> 15:18.618
WE GET FROM THE STATE, SO
I WANT THE MEDICAL BOARD TO SEE

15:18.618 --> 15:20.991
THAT WE HAVE NOTHING
TO HIDE.

15:20.991 --> 15:22.692
EXCEPT FOR THE TRUTH
ABOUT NURSE LAURIE'S MURDER.

15:22.692 --> 15:26.696
WHAT HAPPENED TO NURSE LAURIE
WAS HORRIBLE.

15:26.696 --> 15:29.699
IT'S NATURAL FOR PEOPLE'S
FEELINGS ABOUT IT TO LINGER,

15:29.699 --> 15:31.701
BUT THE POLICE
HAVE INVESTIGATED,

15:31.701 --> 15:33.603
AND THE CASE IS CLOSED.

15:35.265 --> 15:38.608
YOU DON'T TRUST
THE GOOD DOCTOR?

15:38.608 --> 15:41.411
WHY SHOULD I?
HE'S COLD, IMPATIENT.

15:41.411 --> 15:42.642
MUCH LIKE YOUR FATHER,
NO?

15:42.642 --> 15:44.214
REALLY? DADDY ISSUES?

15:44.214 --> 15:46.216
YOU COULDN'T COME UP
WITH SOMETHING MORE ORIGINAL?

15:46.216 --> 15:48.078
SO YOU WANT TO
BE ORIGINAL?

15:48.078 --> 15:50.450
WELL, UNFORTUNATELY,
YOUR WORK DOES NOT REFLECT THIS.

15:50.450 --> 15:53.953
A DISTINCT LACK
OF SELF-ICONOGRAPHY --

15:53.953 --> 15:57.027
AND LOOK AT
THAT ENORMOUS SUN.

15:57.027 --> 15:59.559
OBVIOUSLY, AN
OVER-IDENTIFICATION
WITH THE MOTHER.

15:59.559 --> 16:01.992
GOD, YOU'RE ANNOYING. NO WONDER
I HATED YOU IN COLLEGE.

16:01.992 --> 16:05.395
HEY, DAN.
WHO'S YOUR FRIEND?

16:05.395 --> 16:08.498
WHOEVER IT IS
YOU KEEP TALKING TO?

16:08.498 --> 16:11.441
YOU'RE IN A LOONY BIN, DUDE.
IT HAPPENS.

16:11.441 --> 16:13.643
IT'S SIGMUND FREUD.

16:13.643 --> 16:15.975
SHUT UP.

16:17.147 --> 16:18.278
YOU LYING AGAIN?

16:18.278 --> 16:20.450
HE'S ANALYZING
MY PAINTING.

16:20.450 --> 16:23.613
WHAT'S HE SAYING?

16:23.613 --> 16:26.316
THE USUAL FREUDIAN CRAP.

16:26.316 --> 16:28.018
OH, MAN, I-I-I THINK FREUD
WAS A GENIUS.

16:28.018 --> 16:29.289
THE SCIENCE OF THE MIND.

16:29.289 --> 16:32.262
HEY, YOU THINK
HE'D LOOK AT MY PAINTING?

16:34.524 --> 16:35.625
I DON'T SEE WHY NOT.

16:35.625 --> 16:36.996
[ GROANS ]

16:44.434 --> 16:47.307
THIS WOMAN IS EXTREMELY
TROUBLED, DANIEL.

16:47.307 --> 16:49.039
WHAT'S HE SAYING?

16:49.039 --> 16:51.711
HE SAYS IT'S BEAUTIFUL.

16:57.517 --> 17:02.692
ZOEY?
HER DELUSIONS ARE VERY DARK.
PERHAPS THEY OVERPOWER HER.

17:08.158 --> 17:11.501
DID YOU JUST...
SEE SOMETHING, TOO?

17:11.501 --> 17:13.363
I DON'T SEE THINGS.

17:13.363 --> 17:16.066
I HEAR VOICES.
THERE'S A DIFFERENCE.

17:16.066 --> 17:18.768
DO THE VOICES TELL YOU
TO DO BAD THINGS?

17:18.768 --> 17:21.771
THIS IS MY SIXTH TOUR
OF THIS PLACE.

17:21.771 --> 17:24.144
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

17:33.323 --> 17:35.285
[ ROCK MUSIC PLAYS ]

17:35.285 --> 17:36.556
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

17:37.827 --> 17:39.259
WHERE'S MY PITCHER?
COMING.

17:40.460 --> 17:41.631
ALL RIGHT.
THERE YOU ARE.

17:42.292 --> 17:43.793
EXCUSE ME!
THIS IS A DAIQUIRI.

17:43.793 --> 17:45.635
I ACTUALLY ORDERED
A PIÃ‘A COLADA.
SORRY.

17:45.635 --> 17:48.398
WE'RE NOT DATING,
SWEETHEART.

17:48.398 --> 17:51.070
YOU CAN'T MAKE ME
WAIT ALL NIGHT FOR IT.

17:52.702 --> 17:57.847
AND NOW SHE'S OUT OF BEER.
GREAT.

17:57.847 --> 17:59.849
YEAH, AND IN A SECOND, I'M GONNA
BE OUT OF PATIENCE, TOO,

17:59.849 --> 18:03.553
SO WHY DON'T
YOU SHUT YOUR MOUTH!
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA!
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA!

18:03.553 --> 18:05.455
TRUST ME, PAL. YOU DON'T
WANT TO POKE THIS BEAR.

18:05.455 --> 18:06.856
DONNIE,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

18:06.856 --> 18:08.858
WELL, I CAME BY FOR
THE FRIENDS-AND-FAMILY DISCOUNT,

18:08.858 --> 18:10.720
BUT IT LOOKS LIKE
I BETTER TAP A NEW KEG

18:10.720 --> 18:12.292
AND MAKE THAT
COLADA INSTEAD.

18:12.292 --> 18:14.294
TRUST ME.
I'VE GOT THIS, SO GO.

18:14.294 --> 18:15.795
[ THUD ]
OW!

18:15.795 --> 18:18.828
KATE, HEY. COME HERE.
LET ME DO IT. LET ME DO IT.

18:18.828 --> 18:20.500
YOU TAKE CARE
OF THE BADGE BUNNY

18:20.500 --> 18:22.402
WAITING ON HER APPLETINI.

18:22.402 --> 18:25.305
COME ON.
IT'LL BE LIKE OLD TIMES.

18:25.305 --> 18:27.777
ALL RIGHT, BUT JUST UNTIL
I'M OUT OF THE WEEDS.

18:27.777 --> 18:30.140
OF COURSE.

18:30.140 --> 18:32.442
HEY! INCOMING.

18:41.751 --> 18:43.293
HEY, UM...

18:43.293 --> 18:46.456
THE BLUE PAINT
ON YOUR PORTRAIT --

18:46.456 --> 18:49.329
WAS THAT JUST SABOTAGING
THE WORK,

18:49.329 --> 18:53.333
OR DID IT HAVE
SOME OTHER MEANING?

18:53.333 --> 18:56.506
[ As Daniel ] WERE YOU JUST
SABOTAGING THE WORK,

18:56.506 --> 18:58.468
OR DID IT HAVE
SOME OTHER MEANING?

18:59.569 --> 19:02.542
Anthony: [ LAUGHS ]

19:02.542 --> 19:04.714
DO NURSE RINA.

19:05.545 --> 19:07.777
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

19:07.777 --> 19:10.820
[ As Nurse Rina ] ANTHONY,
HOW ARE WE FEELING TONIGHT?

19:10.820 --> 19:13.723
DID YOU HAVE SOME YUMMY
CHICKEN POT PIE AT DINNER?

19:13.723 --> 19:15.255
TIME FOR YOUR MEDS.

19:15.255 --> 19:16.686
[ LAUGHS ]

19:16.686 --> 19:19.259
UH, DO DR. POOLE.

19:19.259 --> 19:22.432
[ As Dr. Poole ]
SHANNON...

19:22.432 --> 19:26.296
HOW DID THE POT PIE
MAKE YOU...FEEL?

19:26.296 --> 19:28.738
SEXY? I SEE.

19:28.738 --> 19:31.741
AND WHAT SPECIFICALLY
ABOUT THE POT PIE WAS...

19:31.741 --> 19:33.943
SEXY TO YOU?

19:33.943 --> 19:36.746
[ LAUGHTER ]
[ Normal voice ] THANK YOU,
THANK YOU, THANK YOU. THANK YOU.

19:36.746 --> 19:37.907
Man:
CREAK! CREAK! CREAK!
Man #2: YEAH!

19:37.907 --> 19:40.380
NO, NO, NO.
PICK ANOTHER ONE.

19:40.380 --> 19:42.612
[ ALL CHANTING "CREAK!" ]

19:42.612 --> 19:45.184
STOP! I'M NOT DOING CREAK!
JUST FORGET IT.

19:45.184 --> 19:46.916
FORGET IT.

19:46.916 --> 19:50.460
WHO'S CREAK?
I SAID, FORGET IT.

19:50.460 --> 19:52.562
I'LL TELL YOU
WHO CREAK IS.

19:52.562 --> 19:54.264
ANTHONY,
DIM THE LIGHTS.

19:54.264 --> 19:56.566
CAN YOU GIVE ME
A FLASHLIGHT?

20:02.972 --> 20:05.505
BACK IN THE SO-CALLED
DARK AGES OF THIS PLACE --

20:05.505 --> 20:06.876
WE'RE TALKING 1980s --

20:06.876 --> 20:08.878
THEY HAD A SPECIAL WAY
OF DEALING WITH PATIENTS

20:08.878 --> 20:10.540
WHO DIDN'T COOPERATE.

20:10.540 --> 20:13.983
THERE WAS A ROOM AT
THE OTHER END OF THE HOSPITAL --

20:13.983 --> 20:18.848
CREAK'S ROOM --
WHERE HE KEPT HIS DRILL.

20:18.848 --> 20:20.650
WHAT WAS THE DRILL FOR?

20:20.650 --> 20:22.622
HOLES INTO THE BRAIN.

20:25.255 --> 20:27.527
POINT BEING, YOU GOT TO GIVE
THE BAD STUFF A WAY TO GET OUT.

20:29.429 --> 20:32.432
BUT CREAK TOOK YOUR SOUL,
TOO.

20:32.432 --> 20:34.604
YOU'D GO IN THERE
KICKING AND SCREAMING.

20:34.604 --> 20:36.536
YOU'D COME OUT DEAD INSIDE.

20:36.536 --> 20:38.608
OF COURSE, WHEN THE STATE CAME
IN AND CLEANED EVERYTHING UP,

20:38.608 --> 20:40.470
CREAK DISAPPEARED.

20:40.470 --> 20:43.473
SOME PEOPLE
SAID THAT HE DIED.

20:43.473 --> 20:46.416
BUT THAT'S A LIE.
THAT'S A LIE.

20:46.416 --> 20:48.548
SO WHERE IS HE?

20:48.548 --> 20:49.619
WELL, WORD IS
THAT HE TOOK HIS DRILL

20:49.619 --> 20:51.621
AND SET UP SHOP
IN THE BASEMENT,

20:51.621 --> 20:54.384
AND HE'S BEEN THERE
EVER SINCE.

20:54.384 --> 20:57.387
BUT YOU KNOW WHAT I THINK?
NOBODY CARES, VIRGIL.

20:57.387 --> 21:00.029
YOU TOLD YOUR STORY.
NOW SHUT UP.

21:00.029 --> 21:02.832
CREAK'S DOWN THERE,
ALL RIGHT.

21:02.832 --> 21:05.565
BUT HE ISN'T HUMAN.

21:05.565 --> 21:09.339
HE'S PARANORMAL,
SUPERNATURAL,

21:09.339 --> 21:11.841
BECAUSE HE KNOWS
EVERYTHING --

21:11.841 --> 21:14.544
WHAT YOU THINK,
WHAT YOU DO.

21:14.544 --> 21:17.947
AND WHEN YOU STEP OUT OF LINE,
HE'LL WAIT UNTIL NIGHTTIME,

21:17.947 --> 21:24.484
WHEN EVERYTHING'S DARK,
AND HE COMES AND...GETS YOU!

21:24.484 --> 21:27.617
[ SCREAMS ]

21:27.617 --> 21:29.959
ANTHONY,
THAT WASN'T COOL.

21:29.959 --> 21:32.462
THAT WAS AN ACCIDENT.

21:32.462 --> 21:34.664
YOU GUYS
ARE ALL ASSHOLES.

21:38.568 --> 21:40.830
ZOEY. ZOEY.

21:40.830 --> 21:44.404
ZOEY, IT'S OKAY.
IT'S OKAY. I UNDERSTAND.

21:44.404 --> 21:46.005
SOMETIMES,
OUR MINDS CAN MAKE

21:46.005 --> 21:47.877
EVEN A STUPID GHOST STORY
SEEM REAL.

21:47.877 --> 21:52.412
IT'S NOT A STORY.
CREAK IS REAL.

21:52.412 --> 21:55.915
JUST -- JUST TAKE YOUR MEDS
AND ACT NORMAL

21:55.915 --> 21:58.448
SO YOU CAN
GET THE HELL OUT OF HERE

21:58.448 --> 22:01.020
BEFORE HE COMES
FOR YOU, TOO.

22:01.020 --> 22:03.553
CLEAR THE ROOM!
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?
HE CAME FOR YOU?

22:03.553 --> 22:06.025
[ GASPS ]
DON'T TOUCH ME!

22:06.025 --> 22:07.997
GET AWAY FROM ME!

22:19.939 --> 22:21.641
MM.

22:21.641 --> 22:22.642
NO, NO, NO.

22:22.642 --> 22:23.973
MM. NO, TAKE IT.

22:23.973 --> 22:25.515
I COULDN'T HAVE DONE IT TONIGHT
WITHOUT YOU.

22:25.515 --> 22:27.517
SERIOUSLY,
TAKE YOUR SHARE.

22:27.517 --> 22:29.419
[ SIGHS ]

22:29.419 --> 22:31.921
JUST FOR THE RECORD, YOU WERE
THE ONE SAVING MY ASS ALL NIGHT.

22:31.921 --> 22:34.684
OH, YEAH. I GUESS IT WAS
JUST LIKE OLD TIMES THEN.

22:34.684 --> 22:36.025
HEY, I NEVER HAD
ANY ILLUSIONS

22:36.025 --> 22:37.657
ABOUT WHO WAS
THE BETTER BARTENDER.

22:37.657 --> 22:39.529
[ CHUCKLES ] YEAH,
YOU ALWAYS SAID IT WAS YOU.

22:39.529 --> 22:40.860
MM.

22:40.860 --> 22:42.492
THAT'S WHAT I SAID,

22:42.492 --> 22:44.834
BUT I KNEW FROM THE FIRST NIGHT
WE WORKED TOGETHER

22:44.834 --> 22:46.536
THAT YOU WERE
THE REAL DEAL.

22:46.536 --> 22:48.938
MM-HMM.
I WAS JUST FAKING IT.

22:48.938 --> 22:52.472
YEAH, AND ALL THE CUSTOMERS WERE
SO DAZZLED BY YOUR CHARM,

22:52.472 --> 22:54.073
THEY DIDN'T EVEN NOTICE.

22:54.073 --> 22:55.875
I DON'T KNOW ABOUT THAT.

22:55.875 --> 22:58.047
I DO.

23:06.416 --> 23:08.758
WE MADE A PRETTY GOOD TEAM
BEHIND THE BAR.

23:08.758 --> 23:11.090
HMM.
[ BOTTLES CLINK ]

23:25.475 --> 23:27.807
I KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE THINKING.

23:27.807 --> 23:29.579
BEHIND THE BAR,

23:29.579 --> 23:33.513
IN FRONT OF THE BAR,
ON THE BAR...

23:33.513 --> 23:36.446
THAT'S NOT
WHAT I WAS THINKING.

23:36.446 --> 23:37.987
OH.

23:37.987 --> 23:39.118
MAYBE THAT'S WHAT
YOU WERE THINKING.

23:39.118 --> 23:40.820
[ CHUCKLES ]

23:42.992 --> 23:46.696
I WAS THINKING, UM...

23:46.696 --> 23:48.027
THAT IT'S LATE.

23:49.629 --> 23:52.502
AND YOU NEED TO GO.

23:54.433 --> 23:56.806
[ CHUCKLES ]

24:00.710 --> 24:03.212
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

24:05.875 --> 24:07.216
24 HOURS IN THIS PLACE,

24:07.216 --> 24:08.848
AND THE CLOSEST THING
I'VE GOT TO A LEAD

24:08.848 --> 24:10.850
IS A WOMAN WITH SCHIZOPHRENIA
WHO'S CONVINCED

24:10.850 --> 24:13.182
THERE'S A MONSTER
LIVING IN THE BASEMENT.

24:13.182 --> 24:15.184
HAVE YOU CONSIDERED
THE POSSIBILITY

24:15.184 --> 24:17.527
THAT THE MONSTER
IS NOT A DELUSION?

24:17.527 --> 24:20.029
OH, WHAT?
YOU THINK CREAK'S REAL, TOO?

24:20.029 --> 24:23.733
NO,
BUT ZOEY'S BELIEF CAN BE

24:23.733 --> 24:26.496
THE PRODUCT OF HER DREAMS
RATHER THAN HER PSYCHOSIS.

24:26.496 --> 24:28.668
WHICH, ACCORDING TO YOU,
WOULD BE AN UNCONSCIOUS ATTEMPT

24:28.668 --> 24:31.100
TO RESOLVE A CONFLICT
FROM HER PAST.

24:31.100 --> 24:33.703
OR A CONFLICT FROM WITHIN.

24:33.703 --> 24:36.946
PERHAPS ZOEY IS CONVINCED
OF THE MONSTER'S REALITY...

24:36.946 --> 24:40.179
BECAUSE THE MONSTER
IS HER.

24:40.179 --> 24:42.912
A-ARE YOU SAYING
SHE'S THE KILLER?

24:42.912 --> 24:45.915
CREAK MAY REPRESENT THE
DARK SIDE OF HER PERSONALITY --

24:45.915 --> 24:49.088
THE SIDE THAT SHE HERSELF
CANNOT FACE.

24:49.088 --> 24:52.792
YOU MUST TRY TO GET THE PATIENT
TO TALK, DANIEL.

25:12.712 --> 25:13.883
YOU LIKE TO WATCH?
WHAT?

25:13.883 --> 25:16.185
NO. NO.

25:16.185 --> 25:17.647
HEY!

25:17.647 --> 25:19.088
YOU WERE RIGHT
ABOUT THE NURSE'S KILLER.

25:19.088 --> 25:21.651
IT WASN'T THE SWORD-SWALLOWING
GIRL. IT WAS CREAK.

25:21.651 --> 25:24.153
[ SIGHS ]
OF COURSE IT WAS.

25:24.153 --> 25:28.527
OH, THE PARANOID IS NEVER
ENTIRELY MISTAKEN, DANIEL.

25:31.761 --> 25:33.262
WHY WOULD CREAK
TARGET A NURSE?

25:33.262 --> 25:34.964
I THOUGHT THAT --

25:34.964 --> 25:37.306
THOUGHT THAT HE JUST
PUNISHED UNRULY PATIENTS.
HE DOES.

25:37.306 --> 25:39.308
BUT WHAT IF AN UNRULY PATIENT
WAS ABOUT TO KILL HERSELF,

25:39.308 --> 25:40.970
AND NURSE LAURIE
GOT IN THE WAY?

25:40.970 --> 25:43.643
WHO EXACTLY
ARE WE TALKING ABOUT HERE?

25:43.643 --> 25:45.715
ZOEY.
ZOEY TRIED
TO KILL HERSELF?

25:45.715 --> 25:48.848
RUMOR HAS IT THAT CREAK
ALMOST SCARED HER TO DEATH.

25:50.149 --> 25:52.682
AND WHAT,
LAURIE STOPPED HER?

25:52.682 --> 25:54.183
AND THEN SHE GOT DEAD.

25:54.183 --> 25:56.055
SEE,
MY GUESS IS THAT CREAK

25:56.055 --> 25:57.787
DIDN'T APPRECIATE
THE INTERFERENCE.

25:57.787 --> 25:59.989
HOW DO YOU KNOW ALL THIS,
VIRGIL?

25:59.989 --> 26:01.991
I DON'T SLEEP MUCH.

26:01.991 --> 26:04.063
GIVES ME MORE TIME
TO LEARN THINGS.

26:06.035 --> 26:09.568
SO, WHY -- WHY WOULD CREAK
GO AFTER ZOEY?

26:09.568 --> 26:11.140
WHAT, DID SHE --
DID SHE DO SOMETHING WRONG?

26:11.140 --> 26:13.673
MAYBE SHE DIDN'T BELIEVE
HE WAS REAL.

26:13.673 --> 26:15.675
SHE BELIEVES NOW,
THOUGH.

26:15.675 --> 26:17.707
[ LAUGHING ]

26:21.210 --> 26:22.752
Zoey:
VIRGIL'S AN IDIOT.

26:24.153 --> 26:27.687
HE ROAMS THE HALLS AT NIGHT,
LISTENING TO THE NURSES GAB.

26:27.687 --> 26:29.118
AS IF THEY KNOW
ANYTHING.

26:29.118 --> 26:30.790
WELL,
WHAT HE SAID ABOUT CREAK,

26:30.790 --> 26:32.161
AND -- AND -- AND YOU
TRYING TO KILL YOURSELF...

26:32.161 --> 26:35.194
WHO THE HELL ARE YOU
TO ASK ME THAT?

26:42.001 --> 26:43.703
My name
is Daniel Pierce.

26:43.703 --> 26:45.875
I'm working
with Erica's lawyer.

26:45.875 --> 26:47.737
We believe
she was wrongly accused

26:47.737 --> 26:49.739
of Nurse Laurie's murder.

26:49.739 --> 26:51.340
I came here
to find out the truth.

26:51.340 --> 26:54.213
[ CHUCKLES ]
SURE YOU DID.

26:54.213 --> 26:58.217
THE SCHIZO DETECTIVE
AND HIS SIDEKICK, SIGMUND FREUD.

26:58.217 --> 27:01.090
I understand
if you don't believe me,

27:01.090 --> 27:03.122
but I believe you.

27:03.122 --> 27:05.995
I believe Creak is real.

27:05.995 --> 27:08.157
I believe he did something
so horrible to you

27:08.157 --> 27:09.859
that it made you
want to die.

27:09.859 --> 27:12.031
Now, if you tell me about it,
maybe I can help.

27:12.031 --> 27:14.363
THAT'S WHAT
NURSE LAURIE SAID.

27:14.363 --> 27:16.335
SHE ENDED UP DEAD.
RIGHT.

27:16.335 --> 27:18.908
AND ERICA MIGHT
GO TO PRISON FOR THAT.

27:18.908 --> 27:21.310
SHE CAN'T SURVIVE
IN THERE.

27:21.310 --> 27:24.013
ZOEY, YOU SAID
SHE WAS YOUR FRIEND.

27:26.275 --> 27:29.819
SOMEBODY CAME
INTO MY ROOM.

27:29.819 --> 27:32.982
I COULDN'T SEE A FACE,
JUST...

27:32.982 --> 27:35.324
A GLOVE...

27:35.324 --> 27:39.028
AND A SYRINGE
WITH BLUE LIQUID.

27:39.028 --> 27:43.893
I BLACKED OUT, AND I WOKE UP
IN THIS CRAZY ROOM

27:43.893 --> 27:45.895
WITH ALL THESE...

27:45.895 --> 27:48.768
COLORS AND THINGS
CHANGING SHAPE.

27:51.040 --> 27:54.744
I COULDN'T MOVE.

27:54.744 --> 27:55.975
CREAK WAS THERE.

27:55.975 --> 27:57.747
WHAT DID HE LOOK LIKE?

27:57.747 --> 27:59.749
I DON'T KNOW.

27:59.749 --> 28:03.412
HE WAS...
DRESSED ALL IN BLACK.

28:03.412 --> 28:05.955
HIS BREATH...

28:05.955 --> 28:09.118
SMELLED AWFUL, LIKE...

28:09.118 --> 28:12.822
DEATH.

28:12.822 --> 28:15.825
HE HAD HIS DRILL, AND HE JUST --
HE KEPT SAYING

28:15.825 --> 28:17.696
I HAD TO FORGET
WHAT I SAW THAT NIGHT

28:17.696 --> 28:19.729
OR HE WAS GONNA
TAKE THE MEMORY OUT HIMSELF.

28:19.729 --> 28:21.270
WHAT DID YOU SEE?

28:21.270 --> 28:22.932
I DIDN'T SEE ANYTHING.

28:22.932 --> 28:26.806
BUT CREAK
SAID I WAS LYING.

28:26.806 --> 28:29.138
HE SAID IF I EVEN THOUGHT
ABOUT TELLING ANYONE ELSE

28:29.138 --> 28:31.340
THAT HE WOULD KNOW,
AND HE WOULD TAKE ME AGAIN.

28:33.813 --> 28:38.487
I JUST COULDN'T GET IT
OUT OF MY MIND --

28:38.487 --> 28:41.120
HOW I'D NEVER BE
FREE FROM HIM.

28:41.120 --> 28:43.953
I JUST...

28:43.953 --> 28:48.427
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]
I FELT HOPELESS.

28:48.427 --> 28:51.330
AND THAT'S WHY
YOU TRIED TO HANG YOURSELF.

28:53.502 --> 28:57.036
NURSE LAURIE WALKED IN
BEFORE I COULD FINISH THE JOB.

28:57.036 --> 28:58.507
DID YOU TELL HER
ABOUT CREAK?

29:01.841 --> 29:03.843
SHE BELIEVED ME.

29:06.015 --> 29:07.346
SHE SAID SHE KNEW
WHAT TO DO,

29:07.346 --> 29:09.478
AND I WOULDN'T HAVE TO WORRY
ABOUT CREAK ANYMORE.

29:12.782 --> 29:16.786
THAT WAS THE LAST THING
SHE SAID TO ME.

29:19.328 --> 29:21.330
IT'S PSYCHOLOGICAL
TORTURE.

29:21.330 --> 29:24.063
THEY'RE USING AN OLD HOSPITAL
LEGEND ABOUT A MONSTER

29:24.063 --> 29:25.835
to punish patients
who don't cooperate.

29:25.835 --> 29:28.367
NURSE LAURIE FOUND OUT ABOUT IT,
AND THAT'S WHY SHE WAS KILLED.

29:28.367 --> 29:29.869
KILLED BY WHOM, DANIEL?
THAT'S KIND OF IMPORTANT.

29:29.869 --> 29:32.201
I DON'T KNOW YET, I --
B-BUT I HAVE SOME LEADS.

29:32.201 --> 29:34.373
ZOEY SAID SHE WAS INJECTED
WITH A BLUE LIQUID

29:34.373 --> 29:35.975
BEFORE CREAK DRAGGED HER
INTO THE BASEMENT.

29:35.975 --> 29:38.147
I-I-I-I THINK THE BLUE LIQUID
WAS PERINADROL.

29:38.147 --> 29:39.478
IT'S A DATE-RAPE DRUG
THAT THEY PROBABLY MIXED

29:39.478 --> 29:41.881
WITH LSD OR SOMETHING.
LSD?

29:41.881 --> 29:44.413
DANIEL, YOU'RE NOT MAKING
ANY SENSE. SLOW DOWN.

29:44.413 --> 29:46.415
THEY'RE ABUSING PATIENTS, RUBEN.
DO YOU UNDERSTAND THAT?

29:46.415 --> 29:49.358
[ DOOR OPENS ]
SEE? HE STOLE THE PHONE
RIGHT OUT OF MY PURSE.

29:49.358 --> 29:51.090
Daniel, what's going on?
I JUST NEED
A LITTLE MORE TIME.

29:51.090 --> 29:53.222
THIS ISN'T OUR IDEA
OF COOPERATION, DANIEL.

29:53.222 --> 29:55.264
I WARNED YOU
THERE WOULD BE CONSEQUENCES.
[ GRUNTS ]

29:55.264 --> 29:56.996
NO! NO NEEDLES!

29:56.996 --> 29:58.227
DANIEL!

29:58.227 --> 30:00.099
WAIT A SECOND --
YOU'RE TELLING ME

30:00.099 --> 30:01.370
THAT YOU LET HIM
CHECK HIMSELF

30:01.370 --> 30:04.073
INTO A MENTAL HOSPITAL
COMPLETELY ALONE?

30:04.073 --> 30:05.274
RUBEN: All right,
you can crucify me later.

30:05.274 --> 30:06.805
Right now,
Daniel needs our help.

30:06.805 --> 30:09.138
I WAS THINKING WE COULD
DRIVE DOWN THERE

30:09.138 --> 30:10.910
AND THEN --
No, Ruben.

30:10.910 --> 30:13.812
THERE'S NO "WE." YOU HAVE HAD
YOUR TIME AT THE WHEEL.

30:13.812 --> 30:15.544
[ SIGHS ]

30:24.223 --> 30:26.225
IT'S A QUIET ROOM,
DANIEL.

30:26.225 --> 30:28.097
GET SOME SLEEP.

30:29.498 --> 30:32.501
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

30:39.869 --> 30:42.111
[ GRUNTING ]

30:43.512 --> 30:44.944
[ SCREAMS ]

30:47.316 --> 30:48.918
[ GASPS ]

30:56.225 --> 30:58.857
I NEED TO SEE
DANIEL PIERCE. NOW.

30:58.857 --> 31:00.029
I'M SORRY.

31:00.029 --> 31:01.891
WE CAN'T COMMENT
ON ANY PATIENT

31:01.891 --> 31:03.392
THAT MAY OR MAY NOT BE --
DR. PIERCE...

31:03.392 --> 31:04.894
IS NOT A REAL PATIENT.

31:04.894 --> 31:06.896
HE DELIBERATELY
HAD HIMSELF CHECKED IN

31:06.896 --> 31:09.068
SO THAT HE COULD INVESTIGATE
THE MURDER OF LAURIE MASON.

31:09.068 --> 31:11.100
HE WORKS
FOR THE F.B.I.?

31:11.100 --> 31:12.501
YES. HE DOES.

31:12.501 --> 31:15.604
AND THE F.B.I. TENDS TO GET
EXTREMELY CRANKY

31:15.604 --> 31:19.408
WHEN IT'S AFTER 1:00 A.M.
AND THEY DON'T GET THEIR WAY.

31:30.459 --> 31:33.963
YOU'RE GETTING
SOME MOVEMENT BACK.

31:33.963 --> 31:36.425
FOLLOW MY FINGER,
DANIEL.

31:45.404 --> 31:47.136
THE PERINADROL
IS WEARING OFF.

31:47.136 --> 31:49.238
THE LSD MAY TAKE LONGER.

31:53.682 --> 31:55.444
[ Distorted ]
DO YOU KNOW WHO I AM?

31:55.444 --> 31:58.617
YOU'RE -- YOU'RE CREAK.

31:58.617 --> 32:00.249
BUT YOU'RE NOT REAL.

32:00.249 --> 32:01.991
NO?

32:04.493 --> 32:06.495
HE'S SUPPOSED TO BE
IN HERE.

32:06.495 --> 32:09.358
OKAY, WELL, EITHER SOMEONE
TOOK HIM OUT OR LET HIM OUT.

32:09.358 --> 32:11.360
IS ALL OF YOUR STAFF
ACCOUNTED FOR?

32:11.360 --> 32:13.702
ONE OF THE NURSES
CALLED IN SICK -- LEX.

32:13.702 --> 32:15.564
OKAY, WELL,
I'M GONNA NEED HIS INFORMATION.

32:15.564 --> 32:17.066
DID YOU GET AHOLD
OF DR. POOLE?

32:17.066 --> 32:18.937
HE'S ON HIS WAY.
ALL RIGHT.

32:18.937 --> 32:20.439
Zoey: CREAK TOOK DAN.

32:20.439 --> 32:21.670
ZOEY.

32:21.670 --> 32:23.672
WHO'S CREAK?

32:23.672 --> 32:26.375
HE'S AN IMAGINARY MONSTER
THAT LIVES IN THE BASEMENT.

32:26.375 --> 32:28.317
IT'S A GHOST STORY
THEY ALL TELL EACH OTHER.

32:28.317 --> 32:29.648
CREAK ISN'T JUST A STORY!

32:29.648 --> 32:32.381
TELL ME MORE
ABOUT THIS CREAK.

32:34.523 --> 32:39.288
YOU HAVE BEEN MAKING ACCUSATIONS
ABOUT MY HOSPITAL --

32:39.288 --> 32:42.291
ABUSE,
THE BLUE MEDICINE.

32:42.291 --> 32:46.265
IT'S TIME FOR YOU
TO FORGET.

32:46.265 --> 32:48.967
NO.

32:48.967 --> 32:50.499
NO, I WON'T.

32:50.499 --> 32:53.442
THEN I WILL
MAKE YOU FORGET.

32:53.442 --> 32:57.176
IT'S...
THAT'S NOT POSSIBLE.

32:58.447 --> 33:00.979
IT'S AN IMPERFECT PROCEDURE,
REALLY.

33:00.979 --> 33:05.314
YOU MAY LOSE OTHER MEMORIES --
YOUR -- YOUR FAMILY,

33:05.314 --> 33:07.986
PERHAPS...

33:07.986 --> 33:09.488
YOURSELF.

33:09.488 --> 33:12.291
AND THEN, OF COURSE...

33:14.063 --> 33:15.664
...THERE'S THE PAIN.

33:18.567 --> 33:21.100
TAKE OFF HIS MASK,
DANIEL.

33:21.100 --> 33:22.771
HOW THE HELL
AM I SUPPOSED TO DO THAT?

33:22.771 --> 33:25.304
BY IDENTIFYING HIM.

33:25.304 --> 33:29.007
THE PERSONA IS HIS POWER.
YOU MUST STRIP IT AWAY.

33:29.007 --> 33:30.609
BUT, JUST THINK.

33:30.609 --> 33:34.743
WHO IS HE?

33:38.016 --> 33:39.518
[ METAL CLINKS ]

33:48.357 --> 33:49.728
AGENT MORETTI?
[ GASPS ]

33:49.728 --> 33:53.262
WHO THE HELL ARE YOU?
I'M DR. MITCHELL POOLE.

33:53.262 --> 33:55.704
SORRY IT TOOK ME SO LONG
TO GET HERE. HOW CAN I HELP?

33:55.704 --> 33:57.406
ZOEY DESCRIBED A ROOM
WITH A FURNACE

33:57.406 --> 33:58.737
AND PIPES
ON THE CEILING.

33:58.737 --> 34:00.339
CAN YOU HELP ME
FIND IT?

34:00.339 --> 34:02.211
THAT SOUNDS LIKE ABOUT
A DOZEN ROOMS DOWN HERE,

34:02.211 --> 34:04.273
BUT WE CAN LOOK.

34:06.645 --> 34:08.517
LAST CHANCE.

34:08.517 --> 34:11.480
TELL ME YOU'LL FORGET
WHAT YOU THINK YOU KNOW.

34:11.480 --> 34:15.484
WHO IS HE, DANIEL?
SOLVE THE PUZZLE.

34:15.484 --> 34:16.655
I-I CAN'T!

34:16.655 --> 34:18.757
THAT'S THE WRONG ANSWER!

34:18.757 --> 34:21.530
YOU MUST.
YOU'RE A SCHIZOPHRENIC, DANIEL.

34:21.530 --> 34:24.733
YOUR MIND CAN ONLY RESIST
FOR SO LONG.

34:24.733 --> 34:27.636
WHERE SHOULD I MAKE MY PERFECT,
LITTLE HOLE?

34:27.636 --> 34:29.498
DO YOU FEEL THAT?

34:29.498 --> 34:31.840
[ METAL SQUEAKING ]
NO, BUT I --

34:31.840 --> 34:33.402
I HEAR IT.

34:33.402 --> 34:36.205
SYNESTHESIA --

34:36.205 --> 34:37.546
IT'S A COMMON EXPERIENCE
WITH LSD.

34:37.546 --> 34:40.549
YOUR BRAIN IS MIXING UP
YOUR SENSES.

34:40.549 --> 34:43.712
YOU'RE HEARING
TACTILE SENSATIONS.

34:43.712 --> 34:46.255
AND SEEING SMELLS.

34:48.217 --> 34:50.359
IT'S TIME FOR YOU
TO FORGET!

34:50.359 --> 34:51.860
THAT LOOKS HOT.

34:51.860 --> 34:53.562
IT LOOKS HOT.

34:53.562 --> 34:56.425
LOOKS --
IT LOOKS SPICY.

34:56.425 --> 34:58.767
YES.
I'M -- I'M...

34:58.767 --> 35:01.430
I'M SEEING CINNAMON.

35:06.475 --> 35:08.837
NOW...
BEG FOR YOUR LIFE.

35:08.837 --> 35:12.181
YOU'RE NOT CREAK.
YOU'RE MARK.

35:12.181 --> 35:13.742
WHAT DID YOU SAY?

35:13.742 --> 35:17.115
YOU SCARED ZOEY INTO
BELIEVING YOU, BUT NOT ME.

35:17.115 --> 35:18.387
YOU'RE NOT GONNA DO THIS.

35:19.588 --> 35:21.590
THEY'LL FIGURE OUT
IT WAS YOU.

35:23.692 --> 35:27.726
DAMN! DAMN IT!

35:27.726 --> 35:29.898
DAMN IT!

35:29.898 --> 35:32.731
ZOEY SAID CREAK'S BREATH
SMELLED LIKE DEATH.

35:32.731 --> 35:36.435
THAT'S WHY YOU CHEW GUM --
TO MASK IT.

35:36.435 --> 35:38.437
SHE TOLD LAURIE, AND LAURIE
FIGURED OUT IT WAS YOU.

35:38.437 --> 35:40.369
SHE CONFRONTED YOU.

35:40.369 --> 35:42.511
DAMN IT!
[ GRUNTS ]

35:43.242 --> 35:46.275
SHE -- SHE HAD
THE LETTER OPENER,

35:46.275 --> 35:47.746
AND -- AND YOU KILLED HER
WITH IT.

35:47.746 --> 35:49.618
ERICA GOT ARRESTED.

35:49.618 --> 35:53.482
YOU -- YOU FIGURED YOU COULD
GET AWAY WITH IT.

35:53.482 --> 35:56.185
I DID GET AWAY WITH IT.

36:03.432 --> 36:04.463
DON'T --
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

36:07.866 --> 36:09.538
AND I'M GONNA GET AWAY
WITH THIS, TOO.

36:09.538 --> 36:11.700
DON'T DO IT.

36:11.700 --> 36:13.572
A NUTJOB ESCAPES
FROM HIS ROOM,

36:13.572 --> 36:15.744
AND HE HANGS HIMSELF.
[ LAUGHS ]

36:15.744 --> 36:18.407
HAPPENS ALL THE TIME.

36:18.407 --> 36:20.749
[ GAGGING ]
PEOPLE WILL SAY
YOU'RE JUST LIKE ZOEY.

36:20.749 --> 36:24.353
[ GRUNTS ] EXCEPT NO ONE'S HERE
TO SAVE YOU.

36:27.956 --> 36:29.518
DANIEL!

36:33.292 --> 36:36.725
[ GASPING ]

36:48.637 --> 36:50.639
SO MARK LEIGHTON,
THE ORDERLY,

36:50.639 --> 36:52.511
OFFICIALLY CONFESSED
TO THE MURDER.

36:52.511 --> 36:54.513
SOLD OUT HIS GIRLFRIEND
IN THE PROCESS.

36:54.513 --> 36:57.516
APPARENTLY,
NURSE RINA HELPED HIM

36:57.516 --> 36:58.787
COVER UP
THE WHOLE THING.

36:58.787 --> 37:00.289
SO ERICA'S CLEARED.
YEAH.

37:00.289 --> 37:01.920
SHE'LL BE RELEASED
FROM JAIL TODAY.

37:03.652 --> 37:05.954
YOU HAD THE WHOLE THING
FIGURED OUT.

37:06.955 --> 37:09.498
EXCEPT WHY MARK TORTURED ZOEY
TO BEGIN WITH.

37:09.498 --> 37:11.260
SAID SHE SAW HIM
STEALING DRUGS.

37:11.260 --> 37:12.631
FROM THE HOSPITAL
PHARMACY?
MM-HMM.

37:12.631 --> 37:13.732
HE SAID HE CAME
OUT THE DOOR,

37:13.732 --> 37:14.733
AND SHE WAS JUST
STANDING THERE

37:14.733 --> 37:16.305
STARING RIGHT AT HIM.

37:16.305 --> 37:18.467
SO HE BECAME CREAK
TO SCARE HER

37:18.467 --> 37:19.638
INTO NOT TELLING ANYBODY.

37:21.310 --> 37:23.772
IRONY IS SHE NEVER SAW HIM
IN THE FIRST PLACE.

37:25.474 --> 37:27.816
WHEN -- WHEN ZOEY HEARS VOICES
IN HER HEAD,

37:27.816 --> 37:29.848
SHE LITERALLY
LOSES AWARENESS

37:29.848 --> 37:31.380
OF WHAT'S RIGHT
IN FRONT OF HER,

37:31.380 --> 37:33.722
BUT, TO HIM,
IT MUST HAVE LOOKED LIKE

37:33.722 --> 37:35.584
SHE WAS STARING
RIGHT AT HIM.

37:35.584 --> 37:36.985
[ CHUCKLES ]

37:36.985 --> 37:39.528
WELL, THAT EXPLAINS MARK.

37:39.528 --> 37:41.530
LET'S TALK ABOUT YOU.

37:41.530 --> 37:44.032
KATE, I'M SORRY I DIDN'T
TELL YOU WHAT I WAS DOING.

37:44.032 --> 37:45.364
BUT, IF I HAD --

37:45.364 --> 37:46.695
I WOULD HAVE STOPPED YOU...

37:46.695 --> 37:50.699
BECAUSE THIS IS BY FAR
THE DUMBEST IDEA

37:50.699 --> 37:52.341
YOU HAVE EVER HAD.

37:56.475 --> 37:58.977
THANK YOU
FOR SAVING MY LIFE.

38:02.280 --> 38:04.783
JUST DON'T MAKE ME
DO IT AGAIN.

38:04.783 --> 38:06.785
[ CHUCKLES ]

38:15.964 --> 38:19.828
SO, HAVE YOU EVER PROSECUTED
A SERIAL KILLER?

38:19.828 --> 38:21.029
[ LAUGHS ]

38:21.029 --> 38:22.501
EH...

38:22.501 --> 38:24.503
IT'S NOT AS EXCITING
AS YOU'D PROBABLY THINK.

38:24.503 --> 38:28.006
OH, YOU'RE BEING MODEST.
IT'S CUTE, THOUGH.

38:28.006 --> 38:30.008
LET ME BUY YOU A DRINK.

38:30.008 --> 38:32.040
I BET I COULD
GET YOU TO TALK ABOUT IT.

38:32.040 --> 38:34.643
SORRY. CAN'T.

38:34.643 --> 38:38.417
WHAT THE HELL ARE YOU DOING
BEHIND MY BAR?

38:38.417 --> 38:41.590
HEY, JOE.
UH, KATE HAD AN EMERGENCY.

38:41.590 --> 38:42.791
SHE ASKED ME
TO COVER FOR HER.

38:42.791 --> 38:44.322
SHE OKAY?
YEAH, A WORK THING.

38:44.322 --> 38:45.454
NOTHING TO WORRY ABOUT.

38:47.696 --> 38:51.029
CHATTING UP
THE FEMALE CUSTOMERS?

38:51.029 --> 38:52.901
IS THAT PART
OF THE ARRANGEMENT?

38:52.901 --> 38:55.764
I WASN'T CHATTING HER UP.
I WAS BEING POLITE.

38:55.764 --> 38:59.107
YEAH, WELL, YOU GOT A HISTORY
OF BEING POLITE.

38:59.107 --> 39:00.108
JOE --

39:00.108 --> 39:01.640
LOOK.

39:01.640 --> 39:03.642
I DON'T KNOW WHY
SHE ASKED YOU FOR HELP,

39:03.642 --> 39:04.943
BUT I GOT IT FROM HERE.

39:12.921 --> 39:16.685
WHATEVER YOU THINK OF ME,
I DESERVE.

39:18.487 --> 39:21.660
BUT IT DOESN'T CHANGE
THE FACT THAT I LOVE KATE.

39:26.364 --> 39:27.596
WELL, THAT EXPLAINS IT.

39:27.596 --> 39:29.938
I HAVE BEEN WORKING ON HIM
ALL WEEKEND.

39:29.938 --> 39:31.800
COULDN'T GET HIM
TO BREAK.

39:38.547 --> 39:42.551
SO...LET ME GUESS --

39:42.551 --> 39:44.382
I'M OFF
TO A NEW HOSPITAL.

39:44.382 --> 39:47.486
CHICAGO GENERAL, ACTUALLY,
IF THAT'S OKAY WITH YOU.

39:47.486 --> 39:48.987
DID THAT
WHEN I WAS TWELVE.

39:48.987 --> 39:51.089
WELL, NOW THEY HAVE
A SURGICAL PROCEDURE

39:51.089 --> 39:52.961
THAT HELPS PEOPLE
WITH O.C.D.

39:52.961 --> 39:54.523
IT'S POSSIBLE

39:54.523 --> 39:56.124
THEY CAN TAKE AWAY
YOUR COMPULSION, ERICA.

39:58.126 --> 39:59.668
TAKE IT AWAY?

40:02.801 --> 40:04.973
LIFE AWAITS.

40:04.973 --> 40:07.135
MEANINGFUL FRIENDSHIPS,
INSPIRING WORK,

40:07.135 --> 40:10.008
INDEPENDENCE,
YOUR PLACE IN THE WORLD --

40:10.008 --> 40:13.882
THEY'RE ALL JUST WAITING
OUTSIDE YOUR DOOR.

40:13.882 --> 40:17.045
NOW IMAGINE IF THAT DOOR
WAS LOCKED.

40:17.045 --> 40:19.618
NO KEY, NO SIDE EXIT --

40:19.618 --> 40:21.790
YOU'RE TRAPPED
WHILE EVERYBODY ELSE

40:21.790 --> 40:23.792
BLOSSOMS AROUND YOU.

40:23.792 --> 40:25.494
THAT'S WHAT IT FEELS LIKE

40:25.494 --> 40:28.927
GROWING UP
WITH A MENTAL ILLNESS.

40:30.659 --> 40:32.160
SO, WHILE GAMMA KNIFE SURGERY

40:32.160 --> 40:33.802
CAN DISABLE
THE NEUROLOGICAL CIRCUIT

40:33.802 --> 40:36.665
WHERE THIS PATIENT'S
O.C.D. IMPULSES FORM,

40:36.665 --> 40:38.507
IT CAN'T MAKE UP FOR LOST TIME.

40:40.669 --> 40:43.912
SURGERY CAN'T TEACH US
HOW TO TAKE CARE OF OURSELVES...

40:46.475 --> 40:49.478
...OR HOW TO RECOGNIZE FEELINGS

40:49.478 --> 40:54.222
LIKE LOVE OR LOSS...
OR POSSIBILITY.

40:54.222 --> 40:58.627
WE ALL HAVE TO FIGURE OUT
WHO WE ARE BEYOND OUR DIAGNOSES.

40:58.627 --> 41:02.491
IT'S A LONG PROCESS
THAT BEGINS

41:02.491 --> 41:06.635
WITH LEARNING HOW TO TRUST
OUR OWN MINDS AGAIN.

41:06.635 --> 41:08.136
OF COURSE, THERE ARE PLENTY
OF MENTAL ILLNESSES

41:08.136 --> 41:10.198
THAT CANNOT BE FIXED
WITH SURGERY.

41:10.198 --> 41:12.140
BUT AS MR. LEWICKI
NO DOUBT DISCOVERED

41:12.140 --> 41:15.003
DURING HIS WHIRLWIND WEEKEND,

41:15.003 --> 41:19.548
NEUROLOGISTS
ARE A CRAZY BUNCH --

41:19.548 --> 41:21.479
CRAZY ENOUGH TO BELIEVE

41:21.479 --> 41:26.014
THAT IF YOU COULD DISCOVER
A VIABLE CURE FOR ONE ILLNESS,

41:26.014 --> 41:28.016
THEN, EVENTUALLY,

41:28.016 --> 41:29.558
YOU'LL DISCOVER
A CURE FOR THE NEXT ONE.

41:32.060 --> 41:34.222
WHICH MEANS...

41:34.222 --> 41:37.225
THERE'S HOPE FOR ALL OF US.
